<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id56dab9ee-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02" identifier="/us/usc/t14/s3905"><num value="3905">§ 3905.</num><heading> Disenrollment</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Members of the Auxiliary may be disenrolled pursuant to applicable regulations.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id56dab9ef-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02">(<ref href="/us/act/1949-08-04/ch393">Aug. 4, 1949, ch. 393</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/63/555">63 Stat. 555</ref>, § 824; renumbered § 3905, <ref href="/us/pl/115/282/tI/s119/b">Pub. L. 115–282, title I, § 119(b)</ref>, <date date="2018-12-04">Dec. 4, 2018</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/132/4236">132 Stat. 4236</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id56dab9f0-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="historicalAndRevision" id="id56dab9f1-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Historical and Revision Notes</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Experience has shown that it is desirable to have a statute definitely providing for separation of Auxiliarists from the organization. 81st Congress, House Report No. 557.</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id56dab9f2-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="id56dab9f3-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">2018—<ref href="/us/pl/115/282">Pub. L. 115–282</ref> renumbered <ref href="/us/usc/t14/s824">section 824 of this title</ref> as this section.</p>
</note>
</notes>
</section>
